---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { framework } from "../../lib/data";
---

<BaseLayout title="Context framework" description="Experimental metadata framework used by the repository.">
  <header class="page-heading shell simple-heading">
    <div>
      <p class="prototype-label">Experimental framework {framework.version}</p>
      <h1>Context metadata framework</h1>
      <p>This table is a temporary fixture. The sections, fields, names, and requirements are not final.</p>
    </div>
    <a class="button secondary" href={`/api/v1/framework/${framework.version}.json`}>Download JSON</a>
  </header>

  <section class="framework-content shell">
    <div class="framework-notes platform-model">
      <h2>Project and visualization scope</h2>
      <p>A project can contain one visualization, a complete ordered or unordered collection, or a sampled index for a very large collection. The table below currently describes shared project context; individual visualizations may add encoding and limitation notes.</p>
      <p>Version 0.4 also distinguishes fictional examples from imported source records, records source provenance, allows explicit “not provided” values, and keeps downloadable media renditions separate from visualization identity.</p>
    </div>
    <h2>Current fields</h2>
    <table class="framework-table">
      <thead><tr><th scope="col">Section</th><th scope="col">Field ID</th><th scope="col">Display label</th><th scope="col">Question / guidance</th><th scope="col">Type</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {framework.presentation.sections.flatMap((section) => section.fields.map((field, index) => (
          <tr>
            {index === 0 && <th scope="rowgroup" rowspan={section.fields.length}>{section.label}</th>}
            <td><code>{field.id}</code></td><td>{field.label}</td><td>{field.help}</td><td>{field.valueType}</td>
          </tr>
        )))}
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="framework-notes">
      <h2>Implementation boundary</h2>
      <p>The framework is stored separately from the website in YAML and JSON Schema. The catalog consumes generated JSON, so this structure can be replaced without rewriting project pages.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>framework/framework.yaml</code> registers sections.</li>
        <li><code>framework/presentation/default.yaml</code> defines labels and guidance.</li>
        <li><code>framework/schemas/</code> defines structural validation.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
